The paper discusses the application of machine learning techniques, such as random forest classifiers and deep neural networks, to predict the amount of damage caused by storms. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of input features and the classification method also suggest that the paper could belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Data Mining (cs.DM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper addresses the issue of imbalanced training data, which is a common problem in machine learning, indicating that it could also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
